nbank „Deutsch-jüdische Quellen aus Palästina / Israel“ enthält neben der Bibliographie eine Auswahl besonders wertvoller und seltener Originale im Volltext.  aGerman-Jewish immigration to Palestine and later to Israel represents an important chapter of Jewish culture, history, and literature. The bibliography extends across genres to collect the writings of immigrants published there between 1890 and 2000.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 4aBibliographie. 4aDeutsch-Jüdisch. 4aGerman-Jewish culture. 4aImmigrant. 4aIsrael. 4aPalestine. 4aPalästina. 4aimmigrants. 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh1 aEdelmann-Ohler, Eva, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWassermann, Henry08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2016z9783110485189oZDB-23-DEG0 cEPUBz97831104334320 cprintz978311025707640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311044175840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110441758423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110441758.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DEGb2016  aZDB-23-DGGb2016